Flaum Leadership > Biography



 SANDER A. FLAUM
CEO of Flaum Navigators, Sander Flaum is a veteran consultant to Fortune 500 companies. Flaum Navigators advises and runs seminars on brand leadership for a broad range of clients in the healthcare arena. Sander is an acknowledged marketing and sales effectiveness coach, motivational presenter and best-selling author.
Sander is a featured speaker for multiple organizations and conducts workshops to stimulate creative innovation. His seminars are credited by clients for helping them exceed expectations, improve sales productivity, and foster leadership values.
Author of two books on leadership and achieving success in challenging times, Sander’s latest book,  The Best Thing That Could Ever Happen To You: How a Career Reversal Can Reinvigorate Your Life is due for release in Autumn 2013, was written to guide business professionals in their quest to re-empower themselves after a job loss or while in the midst of a passionless career. The aim is to help these professionals to rewrite their legacy and move forward with a smooth transition.
Sander’s previous books, Big Shoes: How Successful Leaders Grow Into New Roles (2009, LeaderShape) and The 100–Mile Walk : A Father and Son on a Quest to Find the Essence of Leadership  (2006, Amacom) have been credited by numerous company leaders for providing essential advice on how to tackle the management hurdles of a career. The 100-Mile Walk was awarded the Hazan-Polsky Prize for Outstanding Business Books.
Sander is Founder and Chair of the Fordham Leadership Forum at Fordham’s Graduate School of Business Administration where he serves as an Adjunct Professor. He’s also a member of the NYC Venture Fellows program designed to mentor young entrepreneurs.
Selected both in 2001 and 2011 as the Fordham Business School’s commencement speaker, Sander has also been awarded the Ohio State University’s Professional Achievement Award and the OSU Pacesetter Business Leadership award. He is the author of over 80 published articles on marketing, management, and leadership and writes a monthly column for the American Management Association’s MWorld and Medical Advertising News. Sander also has a weekly radio show, “Leader’s Edge,” which advances the ideas and debate of his “Leader’s Edge” blog.
Sander received his undergraduate degree from The Ohio State University followed by an MBA degree (magna cum laude) from Fairleigh Dickinson University. He went on to work for 18 years at Lederle Laboratories, which merged into Wyeth, then Pfizer. In his capacity as Marketing Director of Lederle Rx and biologic products, Sander was responsible for the introduction of a wide range of products and launches.
Post Lederle, Sander became Chairman and CEO of Robert A. Becker, EuroRSCG – a global advertising, marketing and corporate communications company, where he led a worldwide team of marketing strategists that introduced six blockbuster $2 billion healthcare brands. In 2003, Medical Advertising News named Sander its Man of the Year and Becker its Agency of the Year
For more information on the company, visit the business website at   www.flaumnavigators.com





  







